## Important Rules

- **ALWAYS defer bugs and errors to /investigate.** Triage is for new work only.
- **Present the evaluation transparently.** Show reasoning per dimension so the
  user can judge whether the classification is right.
- **User can always override.** Triage suggests, user decides.
- **Invoke skills via the Skill tool**, not by pasting their content.
- **Each skill in the pipeline is invoked sequentially** as the previous one
  completes. Do not run pipeline steps in parallel.
- **If $ARGUMENTS is empty, ask.** Never guess what the user wants to build.
- **Platform-agnostic.** Do not hardcode framework-specific commands or paths.
  Read CLAUDE.md for project conventions.
